members.name: values
members.comment: Returns an array containing the constants of this enum class, in the order they are declared.

return: an array containing the constants of this enum class, in the order they are declared

members.name: valueOf
members.comment: Returns the enum constant of this class with the specified name. The string must match exactly an identifier used to declare an enum constant in this class. (Extraneous whitespace characters are not permitted.)

param: name - the name of the enum constant to be returned.
throws: IllegalArgumentException - if this enum class has no constant with the specified name
NullPointerException - if the argument is null
return: the enum constant with the specified name

name: javax.tools.Diagnostic$Kind
comment: Kinds of diagnostics, for example, error or warning. The kind of a diagnostic can be used to determine how the diagnostic should be presented to the user. For example, errors might be colored red or prefixed with the word "Error", while warnings might be colored yellow or prefixed with the word "Warning". There is no requirement that the Kind should imply any inherent semantic meaning to the message of the diagnostic: for example, a tool might provide an option to report all warnings as errors.
